          <h3>beware IRC services</h3>
BEWARESERV (beware irc services) is an irc services core written in pascal for undernets P10 
protocol and designed to be scaleable both to large netwoks and to small hardware setups. 
The core is combined with a
number of bots and compiled into an executeable. 
<p>
<hr>
Currently there are four bots BWORLD,AUTH,CHANNEL and CONNECT4
<p>
BWORLD is an operator service bot similar to undernets UWORLD
<p>
AUTH is an authentication service providing login and account management for
the other bots,
<p>
CHANNEL is a quakenet style channel service
<p>
CONNECT4 is a bot that allows users to play the board game connect4 in
channels

<p>
with the release of 2.3 more bots will most likely be introduced.
